Qf2, O-O, 14. c3, trade queens and decent queen side position, but I knew he wouldnt let the queen trade happen so early, and I didnt spend enough time figuring out the alternatives, instead I tried to push his queen around by asking him to give up the center one way or another expecting 12. c3, dxc3, 13. Be3, queen to move.  Obv I didnt put alot of thought into it past this point, and didnt see the next move basically ruining my plan

I should have seen this coming, and how hard my bishop is in trouble.  At this point I think I may have just lost the game, and im scrambling to recover from the mistake.  If i dont move my queen and try to relieve pressure elsewhere, 14. ..., Bg4 and then im boned.  Qf2 (my original plan) is foolish, he takes my bishop and im still rocked, and if I try pressure elsewhere with h3 or the even worse b4, he still wins the bishop, only move is to take his bishop, and try to solidify position later
